HEADWORD: Cufic
<hw>Cu"fic</hw> <pr>(k?`f?k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[So called from
the town of <etsep>Cufa</etsep>, in the province of Bagdad.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to the older characters of the Arabic
language.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>Kufic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

